10:
Phew! Feels good to finally kick back
and relax!
13:
What a surprise adventure that was,
huh? I didn't think the weather could
actually change so fast on the open
seas!
17:
The decision to cut our cruising trip
short and take refuge on this Float
was the correct one, indeed.
21:
We'll probably have to stay the
night. I'll contact Love and have her
tell everyone else what's going on.
25:
Excuse me, are there any inns
around here?
28:
There's a cheap hotel... down the
street... if that works for you...
31:
...Is it just me, or is this Float kinda
depressing? Like, the whole place
feels dead.
35:
I'm more concerned about all the
eyes on us. You think they're just
nervous around strangers?
40:
A group of friends seeking refuge
from a storm stop at a strange
village in the middle of nowhere...
This is exactly like the beginning of a
horror film.
45:
Oh, come on, you've been watching
too many of those.
49:
Let's just... hope things work out for
the best.
55:
If you wanted a late-night snack, 
all you had to do was ask!
59:
Wh-what? 
You're not a normal monster, are you?
71:
Our horror film night has begun!
Though I am... unsure what it is that
we are facing.
74:
Sacrifices... for our Lord... Souls... for
our Lord...
81:
Oh, dear... What should we do? I do
not feel as if we should cut these
people down, at the very least!
86:
Forget cutting them down! We just
gotta cut through them! Follow my
lead!
95:
Hold on, my sensors are picking up
something—
107:
To be more precise, an experiment
that has fused with the power of the
Devourer of Stars.
112:
Like what I ran into on that island 
I washed up on...
115:
I suspect that this particular sample
managed to escape said island and
ended up on this Float.
117:
It perfectly matches the data 
I received from Selene, at any rate.
122:
In other words, this creature is the
reason behind the townspeople's
strange behavior.
127:
Let's show those tentacles who's
boss!
136:
F-for our Lord... 
We must... We must...
141:
Perhaps luring customers in with
your breasts exposed might be the
best strategy.
145:
Eh. I'd rather be known for my
monster cuisine, thanks.
149:
I understand your reservations.
However, as I have learned from
streamers and video bloggers, you
do what you must!
153:
You could take the world by storm if
you so much as showed a sliver of
skin!
158:
Huh... You really think it'd be that
easy?
162:
...Zantetsu, keep tempting my
cooking teacher down that path,
and see what happens.
167:
Th-there is no harm in offering
alternatives in case all else fails!
Bulleta, do you not think so as well?
171:
...Uh. I've got nothing to say about
this. No comment.
176: What... are we doing here? Huh?
182:
For it is I, Denah Selphis, servant of
the one and only KING OF VOID AND
DARKNESS!
190:
Eh, it's a long story. What about you?
Is there a reason why you dropped
by?
194:
Me? Well, I was on my back from my
grandma's place when...
197:
I sensed my king coming from this
direction. I figured I should say hi.
201:
Wait, that's weird. I don't sense my
king anymore...
206:
Denah, do you want some? 
I promise it's good! I really outdid
myself with the soup stock!
212:
We've also got some beer leftover
from our trip!
217:
Oh! If you don't mind, then yeah! 
I'd love a bowl!
222:
Er, maybe it's best if you didn't eat
this, Denah...
226:
Aw, why not? 
Because I'm joining in late?
236: Thanks! Oh boy, it smells great!
240:
*slurp* Wow, it IS good! What kinda
soup is this?
244:
It's an original recipe made out of
the monster we just fought! I think
Love called it... the Devourer of Stars?
254: Oh no, are you allergic to it?
263:
I can't believe it... You taste so good,
my Lord... You even go perfectly with
beer!
267:
Wow, Parfait. Your cooking's so
good, you have Denah practically
committing sacrilege.
272:
Aw, flatterer! I appreciate the kind
words though!
275:
How about the rest of you? Feeling
hungry?
